    "description": {
      "es": "",
      "en": "Return the name of the directory used for temporary files. This defines the default value for the dir argument to all functions in this module. Python searches a standard list of directories to find one which the calling user can create files in. The list is: The directory named by the TMPDIR environment variable. The directory named by the TEMP environment variable. The directory named by the TMP environment variable. A platform-specific location: On Windows, the directories C:\\TEMP, C:\\TMP,..."
